WEBVTT

00:06.466 --> 00:09.082
[ Elevator bell dings]

00:15.349 --> 00:17.260
[ Footsteps echoing ]

00:35.036 --> 00:36.867
[Heart beating]

00:45.630 --> 00:49.339
[ Breathing heavily]

00:49.342 --> 00:51.253
[ Monitors beeping ]

01:23.626 --> 01:27.335
Holder: Alexi Giffords...
nee Alexi Michaelski.

01:27.338 --> 01:28.669
When he's 5,
his pop gets whacked

01:28.673 --> 01:30.163
by mob soldier Stan Larsen.

01:30.174 --> 01:32.005
Alexi gets dumped
into foster care,

01:32.009 --> 01:35.672
grows up hating on Stan Larsen,
biding his time,

01:35.680 --> 01:37.636
and then he moves in
three blocks from him.

01:37.640 --> 01:39.972
And meets Rosie, changes plans.

01:39.976 --> 01:43.218
Why kill dad when you can kill
what's most precious to him?

01:43.229 --> 01:44.719
Taunting him,

01:44.730 --> 01:47.972
drop off his dead kid's
bloody backpack.

01:47.984 --> 01:50.646
Poetic justice.

01:50.653 --> 01:51.813
[ Doorknob rattles]

01:51.821 --> 01:54.608
[Knock on door]

01:57.118 --> 01:59.450
- Hope I ain't interrupting.
- I got the large black.

01:59.453 --> 02:01.489
Holder has the creamer,
seven sugars.

02:01.497 --> 02:03.328
What are you two doing
in there?

02:03.332 --> 02:06.415
Thanks, Duncan.
Keep the change.

02:06.419 --> 02:09.035
[ Laughs] Keep that up.

02:09.046 --> 02:11.378
They're gonna say you broke up
with Sonoma 'cause of me.

02:11.382 --> 02:14.920
Yo, wouldn't be the first time.
You know what I'm sayin'?

02:17.013 --> 02:19.049
Maybe Alexi's mom
knows where he's holed up.

02:19.056 --> 02:20.171
Let's have a chat.

02:20.182 --> 02:21.763
He could be halfway
to Alaska by now.

02:21.767 --> 02:23.098
It's 1:00 am.

02:23.102 --> 02:25.593
[Cellphone ringing]

02:25.605 --> 02:27.220
[Cellphone beeps] Hey, Jack.

02:27.231 --> 02:29.893
You okay?
You don't sound so good.

02:29.900 --> 02:32.277
Well, uh,
check the green suitcase.

02:32.278 --> 02:35.770
It's where I packed all the cold
and flu stuff in there.

02:35.781 --> 02:37.988
Echinacea and myrrh, son.
That's the ticket.

02:37.992 --> 02:39.607
Straight-up
anti-oxidels.

02:39.619 --> 02:41.575
Okay. Well,
I'll pick you up some Tylenol.

02:41.579 --> 02:42.864
[ Paper rustles]

02:42.872 --> 02:45.363
Soon.
I'm still at work.

02:45.374 --> 02:48.116
Are you sure you're okay?

02:48.127 --> 02:49.458
All right.
Try to get some sleep.

02:49.462 --> 02:51.418
I'll be there as soon as I can.

02:51.422 --> 02:53.333
Bye.

02:53.924 --> 02:55.209
Just go, Linden.

02:55.217 --> 02:57.173
Take care of the little man.
I got it.

02:57.178 --> 02:58.258
No, let's go.

02:58.262 --> 03:00.378
I'll get Tylenol
on the way there.

03:00.389 --> 03:01.925
[ Door opens ]

03:05.936 --> 03:07.142
Ain't exactly the highlight
of my life

03:07.146 --> 03:09.432
giving up my kid, okay?

03:09.440 --> 03:10.771
So, the last time you saw him

03:10.775 --> 03:14.267
was when you dropped him off
at that church.

03:14.278 --> 03:16.439
Gave him up when he was 4.

03:16.447 --> 03:18.403
I mean, he's never gonna
forget his new foster dad.

03:18.407 --> 03:20.193
He's touching him at night.

03:20.201 --> 03:21.691
You are a cruel man.

03:21.702 --> 03:23.488
Well, I'm not the one
who left my son behind!

03:23.496 --> 03:25.111
Holder?

03:36.717 --> 03:38.958
l have a son, too.

03:41.055 --> 03:44.343
And I worry, too, about the ways
I've let him down.

03:44.350 --> 03:47.808
The times I wasn't there
for him.

03:47.812 --> 03:50.849
I know what it feels like to...

03:50.856 --> 03:54.019
To think you've failed
your child.

03:56.904 --> 04:00.192
But he came back to you,
didn't he?

04:00.199 --> 04:02.941
That's when you gave him
that photo of him and his father

04:02.952 --> 04:04.613
when he was little.

04:04.620 --> 04:06.952
So he'd know he was loved.

04:08.374 --> 04:11.241
I know he's here, Monica.

04:14.088 --> 04:16.875
He's a good boy.

04:16.882 --> 04:21.000
[Cellphone beeps] He's got nothing to do
with what happened to that Larsen girl.

04:21.011 --> 04:24.344
Holder: This is Detective Holder.
Badge number 4592.

04:24.348 --> 04:27.431
Request backup
to 2212 Carlyle Street.

04:27.435 --> 04:28.675
[Cellphone closes]

04:28.686 --> 04:31.428
It's better if I take him in
than if they find him.

04:34.942 --> 04:37.228
[Stairs creaking ]

04:47.329 --> 04:48.739
[Thud]

05:00.593 --> 05:02.049
Okay.

05:21.322 --> 05:23.278
Mitch:
Hey. You've reached Mitch.

05:23.282 --> 05:24.738
Please leave a message
after the beep.

05:24.742 --> 05:25.902
Thanks.

05:25.910 --> 05:27.241
[ Beep ]

05:27.244 --> 05:28.905
Hey.

05:28.913 --> 05:31.245
It's me.

05:31.624 --> 05:35.208
I'm just calling
to see how you're doing.

05:35.211 --> 05:37.793
I hope okay.

05:40.257 --> 05:42.418
W—we're okay.

05:42.426 --> 05:43.586
Well...

05:43.594 --> 05:45.550
[Chuckling ]
most of the time.

05:45.554 --> 05:47.840
The boys...

05:47.848 --> 05:49.964
[Sighs]

05:49.975 --> 05:53.638
Well, they miss you, babe.

05:53.646 --> 05:54.761
[Bottle thuds]

05:54.772 --> 05:56.353
I miss you.

06:00.903 --> 06:03.064
Um...

06:04.740 --> 06:06.071
[Sighs]

06:06.075 --> 06:08.691
[Voice breaking ]
The things I've done.

06:08.702 --> 06:13.116
They just won't let me go,
you know, and I'm...

06:13.123 --> 06:14.784
[Telephone beeps]

06:14.792 --> 06:16.498
[Sighing]

06:23.801 --> 06:25.462
[ Exhales deeply]

06:25.469 --> 06:27.300
[ "Flood And Fire " plays in background]
I day after day I

06:27.304 --> 06:31.047
J” you know it ain't right I

06:31.058 --> 06:36.769
J” slow as a glass,
you're slipping away J”

06:37.481 --> 06:41.099
J” you're flood and fire J”
[ Sighs]

06:43.612 --> 06:47.070
I You're flood and fire I

06:54.290 --> 06:56.702
[ Indistinct conversations]

06:58.711 --> 07:01.202
[ Remote clicks] Man:
This autumn canvas...

07:01.213 --> 07:03.795
Man #2: 'Cause I've got
this show in October, so...

07:05.301 --> 07:06.757
[ Gunshot]

07:06.760 --> 07:09.092
[Dramatic music plays ]

07:09.096 --> 07:11.553
[ Remote clicks, music stops]

07:23.235 --> 07:25.191
[ Elevator bell dings]

07:49.637 --> 07:51.548
[ Elevator bell dings]

07:54.183 --> 07:55.969
Excuse me.
Sorry.

07:55.976 --> 07:57.136
Hey.

07:57.144 --> 07:59.760
Man: 4, please.

08:06.403 --> 08:09.645
[ Door opens, closes]

08:09.657 --> 08:12.444
Rise and shine, princess.

08:14.328 --> 08:16.614
What, you want room service?

08:16.622 --> 08:19.830
Eggs over easy?
Buttered toast?

08:19.833 --> 08:21.664
[Slams table]
Get up!

08:22.586 --> 08:24.451
[ Exhales slowly]

08:25.714 --> 08:28.046
- I want a soda.
- You don't get a soda.

08:28.050 --> 08:30.462
You don't get shit.

08:32.888 --> 08:35.004
Hell, you don't get to sit
on that chair.

08:35.015 --> 08:36.516
Get up.

08:36.517 --> 08:38.098
Get up.

08:40.270 --> 08:42.397
[ Chair scrapes ]

08:42.398 --> 08:44.684
[Sighs]

08:46.318 --> 08:47.774
[Chair clatters]

08:47.778 --> 08:50.770
[ Door slams ]

08:50.781 --> 08:52.521
You and me...

08:54.868 --> 08:56.324
we're gonna have
a little convo

08:56.328 --> 08:58.990
about your girlfriend, Rosie.

08:58.998 --> 09:00.408
[ Police radio chatter]

09:00.416 --> 09:03.328
Seems like you didn't watch
the tattoo one too many times,

09:03.335 --> 09:04.950
the way you be drawing Rosie...

09:04.962 --> 09:09.422
Half a dozen unis, photo team,
overtime and a half.

09:09.425 --> 09:11.211
He better be our doer, Linden.

09:11.218 --> 09:12.207
[ Paper rustles]

09:12.219 --> 09:13.834
It's preliminary lab work...

09:13.846 --> 09:15.632
Back on Alexi's place...
Rosie's prints turned up.

09:15.639 --> 09:17.254
And I've got his prints
on her backpack

09:17.266 --> 09:18.426
and the super 8 camera.

09:18.434 --> 09:19.970
Don't worry, son.

09:19.977 --> 09:21.933
The lab also have turned up
traces of ammonium hydroxide

09:21.937 --> 09:23.302
on the straps of the bag.

09:23.313 --> 09:26.305
It's the same chemical that was
found under Rosie's fingernails.

09:26.316 --> 09:28.227
[ Paper rustles]

09:28.861 --> 09:30.442
You got eight hours with him.

09:30.446 --> 09:31.686
Why?

09:31.697 --> 09:34.154
He hasn't asked for a lawyer.
We can hold him for 24.

09:35.743 --> 09:37.950
This department's
under the microscope.

09:37.953 --> 09:39.909
No small part of that
your doing.

09:39.913 --> 09:41.414
We do everything by the book.

09:41.415 --> 09:44.828
You got eight...
Then charge him or let him go.

09:44.835 --> 09:47.167
[ Footsteps depart]

09:47.171 --> 09:48.877
[ Door opens, closes]

09:54.845 --> 09:56.585
[Cellphone chimes]

10:01.643 --> 10:03.929
[Cellphone closes]

10:05.647 --> 10:07.638
[Sighs]

10:07.649 --> 10:09.105
Tina: I told you.

10:09.109 --> 10:11.851
[ Indistinct conversation
in distance]

10:11.862 --> 10:15.070
Man: This is unbelievable.
Where's the money?

10:15.074 --> 10:16.405
What did you do with it, then?

10:16.408 --> 10:18.444
I don't have any money.

10:18.452 --> 10:21.740
How am I supposed to pay
for this, then, huh?

10:21.747 --> 10:22.782
Fine.

10:22.790 --> 10:25.406
[Gasps ] Are you serious?

10:25.417 --> 10:27.658
Uh-huh.
God! Jerk!

10:27.669 --> 10:29.170
[Chuckles]

10:29.171 --> 10:31.082
[ Birds chirping]

10:41.934 --> 10:43.890
[ Polish accent]
How could she leave the boys?

10:43.894 --> 10:45.885
I don't understand.

10:45.896 --> 10:48.683
- Tommy and Denny cannot
stay here no more. - Helen.

10:48.690 --> 10:49.941
The boys are doing just fine.

10:49.942 --> 10:51.853
They're staying exactly
where they are.

10:51.860 --> 10:54.192
- Look at this place.
- I'm working on it.

10:54.196 --> 10:56.528
- It's been crazy.
- You're doing a lot for us, Terry.

10:56.532 --> 10:58.693
And it's appreciated.

10:58.700 --> 11:00.827
[ Polish accent] We're just
concerned about you, Stan.

11:00.828 --> 11:02.989
You need support and help.

11:02.996 --> 11:04.372
I know what's best for my boys.

11:04.373 --> 11:07.285
Being in their own home
is what they need right now.

11:07.292 --> 11:09.157
- Why did she leave you?
- Ma...

11:09.169 --> 11:12.252
No, you let him talk.
I want to know.

11:14.216 --> 11:17.174
I got to take care of something
down at the station.

11:17.177 --> 11:18.587
Is everything okay?

11:18.595 --> 11:21.587
Something I should have done
a while ago.

11:21.598 --> 11:22.713
[Sighs]

11:22.724 --> 11:24.134
Always good seeing you, tad.

11:24.143 --> 11:27.977
Oh, that's it, Stan.
Go on, walk out.

11:32.776 --> 11:35.688
[Sighs]

11:42.870 --> 11:45.782
Hi,
um... I need a Coke,

11:45.789 --> 11:48.826
big scrambler with pancakes,
and a number 11.

11:48.834 --> 11:51.041
You got enough to cover that?

11:51.962 --> 11:53.748
See that sign?

11:53.755 --> 11:56.041
It says I have the right
to refuse service to anyone.

11:56.049 --> 11:58.301
[Scoffs] What did I do?

11:58.302 --> 12:00.634
I mean, what the hell?

12:00.637 --> 12:03.925
I got it.
l-l'll pay for her.

12:06.643 --> 12:09.430
Yeah.
She's gonna pay for me.

12:17.738 --> 12:20.480
You can come sit if you want.

12:24.745 --> 12:26.030
Okay.

12:32.002 --> 12:34.288
[Sighs]

12:34.296 --> 12:37.129
So, what? There some guy
waiting in your room?

12:37.132 --> 12:39.919
I mean, it's cool, whatever,
but I got to eat first.

12:42.095 --> 12:45.223
Oh... oh.
[Chuckling] No.

12:45.224 --> 12:47.260
No, it's nothing like that.

12:47.267 --> 12:48.552
No.

12:48.560 --> 12:50.096
Your husband in the room, huh?

12:51.146 --> 12:53.057
I'm not married.

12:54.441 --> 12:57.274
Did he...
beat you or what?

12:57.277 --> 12:59.734
[ lnhales sharply]

12:59.738 --> 13:00.898
[Sighs] No.

13:00.906 --> 13:03.363
He's a good man.

13:03.367 --> 13:05.483
[Chuckles]

13:05.494 --> 13:07.610
Listen, I...

13:07.955 --> 13:11.072
I saw you earlier
down by the pool.

13:11.750 --> 13:13.331
You were with your boyfriend...

13:13.335 --> 13:15.747
That a-hole?
[ Scoffs ]

13:15.754 --> 13:19.918
Okay, look.
FYI... that's not my boyfriend.

13:19.925 --> 13:23.838
Okay? He's just, like, some guy
who had beer or whatever.

13:23.845 --> 13:28.589
Hey, do you want to buy
a postcard from here?

13:28.600 --> 13:31.558
They only cost 50 cents,
and they make great gifts.

13:31.561 --> 13:35.145
Kids love them.
Here. Do you have kids?

13:37.067 --> 13:41.026
What are you, like 17, 18?

13:41.029 --> 13:43.406
Yeah.
[ Scoffs ]

13:43.407 --> 13:46.194
[ Breathes deeply]

13:46.201 --> 13:47.737
[Sniffs]

13:47.744 --> 13:51.328
Child protective services.

13:51.331 --> 13:53.822
Larkspur, Burien...

13:53.834 --> 13:56.246
King County Juvenile Detention.

13:56.253 --> 13:58.335
You get around, Alexi.

13:58.338 --> 14:01.296
[ Scoffs ]

14:07.389 --> 14:10.301
The worst food's at County.

14:11.852 --> 14:14.594
Those bologna sandwiches.

14:14.604 --> 14:16.731
The forever cheese.

14:18.859 --> 14:21.896
[ Breathes deeply]

14:23.280 --> 14:26.192
Case number 78-203.

14:26.199 --> 14:29.737
It's funny how it never
leaves you like a nickname.

14:31.288 --> 14:34.872
So now Slim Shady's gone,
what are you?

14:34.875 --> 14:36.285
Good cop?

14:36.293 --> 14:37.783
I'm not gonna lie to you,
Alexi.

14:37.794 --> 14:39.170
You know the drill, but...

14:39.171 --> 14:42.163
If you care, | get it.
Okay?

14:44.843 --> 14:47.926
What he did to your dad...
Stan Larsen...

14:48.305 --> 14:49.886
He had it coming.

14:49.890 --> 14:52.882
He took away the one person
who could protect you.

14:54.102 --> 14:56.013
Left you with
that emotional cripple...

14:56.021 --> 14:57.227
Your mother.

14:58.273 --> 15:01.310
She gave you up, Alexi.

15:01.318 --> 15:05.106
And the second time,
it wasn't that hard for her.

15:06.031 --> 15:09.944
There's no way
she had your back. Ever.

15:10.786 --> 15:13.027
My mom, too.

15:13.038 --> 15:14.903
CPS must have come
five or six times.

15:14.915 --> 15:16.155
I'd try to cover it up.

15:16.166 --> 15:17.702
Knew the foster house
was gonna be worse,

15:17.709 --> 15:19.324
and it was, right?

15:19.711 --> 15:23.044
Kids aren't fools.
We know.

15:23.590 --> 15:25.501
I must have run away
half a dozen times,

15:25.509 --> 15:29.047
but in the end, she gave me up.
That's what they do.

15:29.388 --> 15:32.050
It wasn't fair.

15:33.308 --> 15:35.720
Rosie had everything.

15:35.727 --> 15:38.343
She had a family who loved her.

15:38.355 --> 15:41.062
A dad who loved her,
and she loved him, too.

15:41.066 --> 15:42.681
[ Laughs]

15:42.692 --> 15:45.479
No, she didn't.

15:46.613 --> 15:49.355
Rosie hated her parents.

15:49.366 --> 15:50.947
What do you mean?

15:51.535 --> 15:54.618
Whatever.
I'm done talkin'... Barbie.

15:56.206 --> 15:58.572
Did you tell her what Stan did
to your father?

15:58.583 --> 16:00.039
No.

16:00.043 --> 16:02.785
Then why'd she hate her family?

16:02.796 --> 16:05.788
You gonna charge me?

16:05.799 --> 16:07.255
If you think you have
something on me,

16:07.259 --> 16:10.217
then charge me,
because otherwise...

16:10.220 --> 16:13.132
Another two hours,
and I walk.

16:26.778 --> 16:28.769
Give me a cigarette.

16:28.780 --> 16:30.395
Please.

16:37.372 --> 16:39.328
Kid's lying.

16:43.211 --> 16:44.826
Rosie had secrets.

16:44.838 --> 16:46.920
Sterling said as much.

16:47.799 --> 16:49.300
Bank account, Beau Soleil,

16:49.301 --> 16:51.838
burner phone she used
the night she died.

16:51.845 --> 16:53.836
All of this six months
before she was killed.

16:53.847 --> 16:55.257
Something changed in that time.

16:55.265 --> 16:57.722
Maybe Alexi told her
about Stan's past.

16:57.726 --> 16:59.842
Made her turn on him.

16:59.853 --> 17:02.686
Mitch wasn't a part of it.

17:02.689 --> 17:05.522
Why did Rosie hate her, too?
It doesn't add up.

17:09.821 --> 17:11.322
Where's his phone?

17:11.323 --> 17:13.279
Processing,
along with his other stuff.

17:13.283 --> 17:15.114
Why?

17:15.118 --> 17:16.574
If she called him
or texted him,

17:16.578 --> 17:18.660
we could do a reverse look-up
on the burner phone.

17:18.663 --> 17:20.324
They rode bikes
in the park together.

17:20.332 --> 17:21.822
She had to call him
at least once.

17:21.833 --> 17:23.164
Want to get a warrant?

17:23.168 --> 17:25.454
No. Ray can do a download
without it.

17:25.462 --> 17:27.544
Won't be able to use it
in court.

17:27.547 --> 17:29.503
If we get a confession,
we won't need to.

17:29.508 --> 17:30.668
Come on, Linden.

17:30.675 --> 17:32.540
Carlson's looking for any reason
to sink the case.

17:32.552 --> 17:33.962
Why's Carlson gonna find out?

17:35.764 --> 17:38.255
Just keep your mouth shut.
We'll be fine.

17:39.643 --> 17:41.679
[ Door opens ]

17:44.606 --> 17:45.891
[ Police radio chatter]

17:46.525 --> 17:48.891
- Mr. Larsen.
- I got to talk to you.

17:48.902 --> 17:49.812
Uh, come with me to my office.

17:49.819 --> 17:51.810
You asked me before
about my past,

17:51.821 --> 17:53.277
if it had anything
to do with... with...

17:53.281 --> 17:54.782
what happened to Rosie.

17:54.783 --> 17:57.650
I want to give you some names.

17:57.661 --> 17:59.652
Some people who have ideas
about me...

17:59.663 --> 18:02.655
about things I did.
May... may I...

18:03.375 --> 18:04.956
we're taking care of this,
Mr. Larsen.

18:04.960 --> 18:06.325
You need to leave.

18:10.674 --> 18:13.165
That's Michaelski's boy.

18:16.680 --> 18:18.762
We've got this.

18:20.392 --> 18:23.179
It's better if you go now.
Please.

18:23.186 --> 18:26.178
Mr. Larsen. Please.

18:37.158 --> 18:39.069
Linden.

18:41.830 --> 18:44.071
[ Breathes deeply]

18:49.879 --> 18:52.495
Mind if I smoke?

18:52.507 --> 18:55.999
Uh... no, no.
I don't mind.

18:56.386 --> 18:58.843
[Lighter clicks]

18:59.556 --> 19:01.638
You visiting someone?

19:04.769 --> 19:07.556
Those things will kill ya.

19:07.564 --> 19:09.179
Kind of a family tradition.

19:09.190 --> 19:11.852
My brother's here for chemo.

19:11.860 --> 19:14.101
I know... I should probably quit
one day, right?

19:17.991 --> 19:22.860
I'm sure your brother...
appreciates you being here.

19:23.330 --> 19:25.036
Well, tell that to him.

19:25.040 --> 19:26.996
It's nothing to be here.

19:27.000 --> 19:29.491
To show up.
We're all here.

19:29.502 --> 19:32.289
The whole family.

19:32.297 --> 19:34.754
That's what you do, right?

19:34.758 --> 19:36.373
You show up.

19:40.680 --> 19:42.420
Do you, um...

19:42.432 --> 19:45.174
want me to get you someone?

19:46.227 --> 19:47.478
I, uh...

19:47.854 --> 19:50.061
can do that.

19:51.274 --> 19:53.014
No.

20:01.201 --> 20:03.112
Ray:
I got into Alexi's voicemail.

20:03.119 --> 20:05.235
Rosie called him twice
on October 5th.

20:05.246 --> 20:06.907
Second time,
she left a message.

20:06.915 --> 20:08.871
1:14 am,
check it out.

20:08.875 --> 20:10.160
[Click]

20:10.168 --> 20:12.910
[ Machinery humming ]

20:13.380 --> 20:14.870
What's that?

20:14.881 --> 20:18.874
I don't know.
Maybe some kind of generator.

20:18.885 --> 20:20.500
Can you play it again?

20:20.512 --> 20:21.501
Yeah.

20:21.513 --> 20:23.094
[Click]

20:23.098 --> 20:24.884
[ Thud]

20:24.891 --> 20:26.392
That sounds
like a sliding door.

20:26.393 --> 20:29.385
It could be from
inside the casino. Hotel?

20:29.396 --> 20:30.852
- Mm-hmm.
- I'll look into it.

20:30.855 --> 20:32.356
Here it comes.

20:32.357 --> 20:34.473
Rosie: Oh, my God, Alexi,
where are you?

20:34.484 --> 20:35.269
[ Panting ]

20:35.276 --> 20:38.234
I'm not even supposed to
be here. I saw him again.

20:38.238 --> 20:40.854
Lex, lam in so much trouble
if anybody finds out I'm here.

20:40.865 --> 20:44.278
Please... please call me
the second you get this.

20:45.745 --> 20:48.828
I can't talk anymore.
God, please, Lex, help me!

20:53.128 --> 20:56.370
Please... please call me
the second you get this.

20:56.381 --> 20:57.712
[Click]

20:57.716 --> 21:00.503
Sarah: Rosie was scared
and alone.

21:00.510 --> 21:06.255
And she turned to you.
She trusted you.

21:06.266 --> 21:09.884
You didn't put her
in that lake, Alexi.

21:11.604 --> 21:13.936
"I saw him again."
Who was she talking about?

21:13.940 --> 21:14.725
[Click]

21:14.733 --> 21:18.021
I'm not even supposed to
be here, Lex, I saw him again.

21:18.027 --> 21:19.233
[Click]

21:19.237 --> 21:21.694
Rosie called you earlier
that night.

21:21.698 --> 21:25.441
Same call, same time,
every Friday night,

21:25.452 --> 21:28.034
from her to you.

21:28.705 --> 21:30.445
You know what I think?

21:32.041 --> 21:32.996
I think you didn't want her
to walk alone

21:33.001 --> 21:34.832
to the ferry at nights.

21:34.836 --> 21:36.622
She went to the casino
every Friday night,

21:36.629 --> 21:40.838
and you drove her to the ferry,
didn't you?

21:41.134 --> 21:43.341
You wanted to hate her,
but you couldn't?

21:43.344 --> 21:44.049
We know Rosie
was in your apartment.

21:44.053 --> 21:45.668
Her prints were there.

21:45.680 --> 21:47.545
Then you left
her there alone...

21:47.557 --> 21:51.391
scared, trapped,
you piece of shit.

21:51.394 --> 21:53.225
- You let her die!
- No, I called her back!

21:53.229 --> 21:54.685
What happened?

21:54.689 --> 21:56.020
She...

21:59.569 --> 22:01.685
She didn't pick up.

22:01.696 --> 22:04.312
So, what? You took off?
Figured it wasn't your problem?

22:04.324 --> 22:06.189
No. I waited at the dock
all night,

22:06.201 --> 22:07.486
and she never came back.

22:07.494 --> 22:08.984
Why'd you drop
her backpack off?

22:08.995 --> 22:11.236
I didn't, okay?!
It wasn't me who did that!

22:11.247 --> 22:13.329
Who was she scared of, Alexi?

22:15.168 --> 22:18.001
Who'd she mean by "him"?
"I saw him again."

22:18.004 --> 22:19.244
I don't know.

22:19.255 --> 22:21.416
She must have told you.

22:21.424 --> 22:23.665
Think.

22:23.676 --> 22:27.419
[Sighing]

22:33.978 --> 22:38.062
We were waiting in the drop-off
lane at the ferry that night.

22:38.066 --> 22:39.727
She was laughing.

22:39.734 --> 22:41.725
She got down in the seat
like she didn't want to be seen,

22:41.736 --> 22:43.897
but it wasn't like
she was scared or nothing.

22:43.905 --> 22:45.361
What made her duck down?

22:45.365 --> 22:48.232
Come on, Alexi.
It had to be something.

22:51.746 --> 22:53.987
We will protect you.

22:54.749 --> 22:56.580
Whoever it was.

22:56.584 --> 22:58.324
She was alone and scared,
and she called you.

22:58.336 --> 23:00.122
She trusted that
you would be there for her.

23:00.129 --> 23:01.255
Be there now.

23:01.256 --> 23:02.291
[ Door opens ]

23:02.298 --> 23:04.163
Let's go, Linden.
Time's up.

23:04.175 --> 23:05.585
No! Not yet!

23:05.593 --> 23:07.458
Come on. His lawyer's here.
His mom put in a call.

23:07.470 --> 23:08.755
You didn't call the police
when you got her message

23:08.763 --> 23:09.752
because they let you down
so many times

23:09.764 --> 23:11.004
when your father was killed.

23:11.391 --> 23:13.757
You had nobody.
All Rosie has is you.

23:13.768 --> 23:15.224
Don't let her down.

23:15.228 --> 23:17.765
Who was she scared of, Alexi?
Tell me.

23:17.772 --> 23:19.512
Moss: Lieutenant,
I'd like to talk to my client.

23:20.316 --> 23:22.272
Now.

23:25.613 --> 23:27.990
If you'll excuse us.

23:36.040 --> 23:37.621
[Sighs]

23:38.877 --> 23:40.617
[ Door closes]

23:46.259 --> 23:48.420
[ Horn honks]

23:48.428 --> 23:50.339
[ Indistinct conversations]

23:56.477 --> 23:58.433
[ Engine turns over]

24:27.634 --> 24:30.501
Janek's place.
Great.

24:32.472 --> 24:34.588
They're gonna be holding him up
here for a while.

24:34.599 --> 24:36.965
Deprogramming him.

24:41.522 --> 24:44.434
Thanks for stopping by, mom.

24:48.863 --> 24:51.855
What is it, papa?

24:53.117 --> 24:55.859
Y-you living here
with Stan...

24:56.287 --> 24:58.073
Don't you see
it don't look right?

24:58.081 --> 25:00.367
That's why we're worried,
me and your ma.

25:00.375 --> 25:01.865
I'm helping him with the boys.

25:02.460 --> 25:06.123
So what happened to that guy,
the big shot you were seeing?

25:06.130 --> 25:07.631
Hmm?

25:07.632 --> 25:10.123
You still waiting for him
to come around?

25:10.134 --> 25:13.217
I don't want to talk about him.

25:13.221 --> 25:17.464
He's not coming.
Like the other guy.

25:18.559 --> 25:22.143
| wish things were different
for you, sweetheart.

25:22.855 --> 25:24.595
Iwish...

25:25.316 --> 25:28.103
l-l wish
you weren't alone.

25:29.445 --> 25:32.107
I'm not alone, papa.

25:32.115 --> 25:34.276
Helen:
[Speaks Polish ]

25:49.173 --> 25:50.333
[ Door closes]

25:51.384 --> 25:54.842
[ "Gloria" plays]
I was it something that they said? I

25:54.846 --> 25:58.338
[ Laughs] I all the
voices in your head I

25:58.349 --> 26:02.763
I they're calling Glori—a-a-a I

26:02.770 --> 26:04.101
[ Laughing ]

26:04.105 --> 26:05.220
I Gloria I

26:05.231 --> 26:08.473
That was wonderful!
That was excellent!

26:08.901 --> 26:10.607
Well, yeah.

26:10.611 --> 26:13.193
I have never even taken a voice
lesson, if you can believe it.

26:13.197 --> 26:14.903
[ Both laugh]

26:15.658 --> 26:17.990
So, how old is your kid?

26:18.828 --> 26:21.160
Your age.

26:21.164 --> 26:23.155
So you skipped out on her
and the hubsters?

26:23.166 --> 26:25.202
That's cold.

26:26.669 --> 26:31.709
She left.
My daughter left.

26:33.134 --> 26:36.672
So, what, you're, like,
on some mission to find her

26:36.679 --> 26:38.886
or something lame like that?

26:39.390 --> 26:40.550
Look, I'm not a rat.

26:40.558 --> 26:42.264
So if that's what
you're expecting,

26:42.268 --> 26:44.304
I mean, I'm not gonna help you.

26:45.772 --> 26:48.104
Why did you leave?

26:49.734 --> 26:51.941
Waitress:
You ladies want anything else?

26:52.320 --> 26:54.527
Um... no.

26:54.530 --> 26:55.986
I'm gonna puke
if I eat anything else.

26:55.990 --> 26:58.106
[Chuckles]
No, just the check.

27:00.369 --> 27:02.860
[ Paper rustles]

27:02.872 --> 27:03.782
Hey.

27:03.790 --> 27:05.155
I'm staying at the motel, too,

27:05.166 --> 27:09.205
and I'm... I'm just above
the pool, and I'm in room 214.

27:11.756 --> 27:14.463
And I'm probably gonna be
back here for dinner.

27:14.467 --> 27:15.673
[Chuckling] I guess.

27:16.427 --> 27:19.214
My boyfriend's probably back
by now, so...

27:20.056 --> 27:21.216
I'll see ya.

27:21.224 --> 27:22.304
Okay.

27:32.026 --> 27:32.981
Hi.

27:32.985 --> 27:34.441
Hi.

27:34.445 --> 27:35.560
Hey.

27:35.571 --> 27:36.560
[Chuckles]

27:36.572 --> 27:37.948
You look great, Eve.

27:38.699 --> 27:40.155
Thanks.

27:40.159 --> 27:41.490
Sit down.

27:44.372 --> 27:46.533
I don't have much time.

27:47.125 --> 27:49.958
It's the usual...
two sweet'n lows.

27:52.380 --> 27:54.086
I wasn't sure you'd come.

27:54.090 --> 27:55.250
What, are you kidding?

27:55.258 --> 27:57.294
After so many years
of radio silence?

27:57.301 --> 27:58.381
Why would I miss this?

27:59.887 --> 28:01.263
How's Kurt?

28:01.264 --> 28:03.004
You really want to know?

28:03.349 --> 28:04.555
No.

28:04.559 --> 28:06.595
Then let's not do that.

28:07.270 --> 28:09.477
DA's office suits you.

28:09.480 --> 28:10.595
I love it.

28:10.606 --> 28:12.938
It's a lot more satisfying
than politics.

28:12.942 --> 28:15.308
I actually really make
a difference.

28:16.487 --> 28:18.068
I'm sure you do.

28:19.866 --> 28:22.653
Are you still married
to your job, Jamie?

28:23.995 --> 28:26.111
Let's talk about you.

28:26.122 --> 28:27.282
Your work.

28:29.625 --> 28:31.661
DA's office still taking heat

28:31.669 --> 28:33.910
for dropping charges
against Darren?

28:35.590 --> 28:38.502
What do you want, Jamie?

28:40.761 --> 28:43.377
You don't have a fever anymore?

28:43.389 --> 28:45.801
Good. That's great.

28:45.808 --> 28:49.926
Uh, I'll be home soon.
Just as soon as I can.

28:49.937 --> 28:52.053
Okay.

28:52.064 --> 28:53.395
[Cellphone closes]

28:53.399 --> 28:57.108
[ Rattling]

29:00.198 --> 29:01.358
[ Lid closes]

29:01.365 --> 29:04.277
[ Plastic rustles]

29:05.161 --> 29:06.150
You want a smoke?

29:06.162 --> 29:07.572
Mnh-mnh.

29:07.872 --> 29:09.533
You sure you don't want
a cigarette?

29:09.540 --> 29:11.155
Holder.

29:11.876 --> 29:15.289
It's just a matter of time
before you're back in the fold.

29:18.758 --> 29:21.124
You know, Linden,
you should live a little.

29:21.135 --> 29:23.501
Smoking isn't how
I define living.

29:23.512 --> 29:24.501
All right.

29:24.513 --> 29:25.969
Just don't go all
"falling down" on me

29:25.973 --> 29:28.134
'cause you can't get your fix.

29:31.312 --> 29:33.348
So, how's little man?

29:34.815 --> 29:36.601
He's better.

29:38.778 --> 29:40.359
He's probably just
trying to dodge school.

29:40.363 --> 29:41.853
He has an algebra quiz
tomorrow.

29:41.864 --> 29:43.365
You should tell him to call me.

29:43.366 --> 29:46.403
Since I aced algebra last time.

29:55.795 --> 29:57.877
All right. [Sighs]

29:59.048 --> 30:00.128
What are you doing?

30:00.132 --> 30:01.997
Hmm? I'm gonna call
the station.

30:02.009 --> 30:05.001
Have the unis send over a car.

30:05.012 --> 30:07.719
You go check up on Jack.
I got this.

30:09.558 --> 30:12.265
I'll make sure Alexi
doesn't leave town.

30:20.152 --> 30:22.438
Don't worry about me.

30:22.446 --> 30:24.778
I never do.
[Chuckles]

30:24.782 --> 30:26.568
Thank you.

30:29.537 --> 30:31.949
[ Car door closes]

30:41.924 --> 30:43.505
[ Door locks]

30:44.385 --> 30:46.171
Jack.

30:50.808 --> 30:52.594
[Gasps]

30:52.601 --> 30:54.387
What are you doing here?

30:55.271 --> 30:58.308
He had 103 fever
when I got here.

30:58.941 --> 31:00.181
Where were you?

31:01.193 --> 31:02.399
You have to go.

31:02.403 --> 31:05.236
You got nothing here,
not even a thermometer.

31:05.239 --> 31:07.150
What the hell is going on,
Sarah?

31:07.158 --> 31:08.568
Maybe you didn't know
where to look

31:08.576 --> 31:10.191
because you don't live here!

31:10.202 --> 31:11.988
I do.
| live here with my son.

31:11.996 --> 31:13.657
You call this living?

31:15.249 --> 31:16.659
Look.

31:16.667 --> 31:18.328
I don't want to fight with you,

31:18.336 --> 31:19.826
but Jack's been calling me.

31:19.837 --> 31:21.043
He's scared, confused...

31:21.047 --> 31:23.629
You had a lawyer call me
and threaten me!

31:23.632 --> 31:24.838
All I want

31:24.842 --> 31:26.707
is to be a part
of his life, okay?

31:27.053 --> 31:28.759
It's time.

31:31.432 --> 31:32.922
[Dialing]

31:32.933 --> 31:33.922
What are you doing?

31:33.934 --> 31:35.094
This is Detective Sarah Linden.

31:35.102 --> 31:37.434
I need a unit
at 392 McCarl Avenue.

31:37.438 --> 31:38.518
Jesus, Sarah...

31:38.522 --> 31:40.854
I told you if you ever came near
my son I'd have you arrested.

31:40.858 --> 31:41.938
I'm going.

31:41.942 --> 31:44.809
Okay? I'm leaving.

31:55.247 --> 31:58.284
Cancel it.
No. C-cancel it.

32:00.669 --> 32:02.205
You care more
about that dead girl

32:02.213 --> 32:04.295
than you do about your own son.

32:06.801 --> 32:10.544
[ Door opens, closes]

32:25.111 --> 32:28.228
Alexi: Don't turn around.
Just drive.

32:32.535 --> 32:33.900
[ Engine turns over]

32:40.501 --> 32:43.664
Hey, you will not believe
what I found out.

32:45.923 --> 32:48.460
You, uh... you want...
you want me to get the nurse?

32:48.467 --> 32:50.458
[Sobbing] No.

32:50.469 --> 32:52.630
I don't want a nurse.

32:53.681 --> 32:56.889
[Sobs]

32:57.143 --> 33:00.306
Not like this.

33:00.312 --> 33:02.052
[Sobbing ]

33:17.621 --> 33:20.203
You want the bed up or down?

33:27.465 --> 33:29.922
[Curtain scrapes]

33:39.059 --> 33:43.644
I knew this guy, worked at
the Boeing plant for 35 years.

33:43.647 --> 33:45.308
One of those guys.

33:45.316 --> 33:46.305
Decorated vet.

33:46.317 --> 33:49.184
I don't want to hear it, Jamie.

33:49.195 --> 33:51.686
I'm talking
about my grandfather.

33:52.865 --> 33:54.571
Ted.

33:55.493 --> 33:56.903
I was in the third grade

33:56.911 --> 33:59.152
when the accident
at the plant happened.

33:59.788 --> 34:02.700
I watched him lose everything.

34:02.708 --> 34:07.543
His wife, house...
his job.

34:07.546 --> 34:09.161
He was dying.

34:09.173 --> 34:11.255
Right there in front of me...

34:11.258 --> 34:14.716
until he started to fight back.

34:14.720 --> 34:17.507
He fought like
the son of a bitch he was.

34:19.517 --> 34:22.008
And he got it all back, Darren.

34:23.103 --> 34:24.684
Used to always say,

34:25.314 --> 34:27.555
bad luck either destroys you...

34:29.151 --> 34:31.984
or it makes you the man
you really are.

34:33.656 --> 34:37.444
I'm not the man
your grandpa Ted was.

34:41.789 --> 34:43.575
How about this?

34:46.544 --> 34:48.910
The man you're conceding
the race to...

34:49.296 --> 34:52.254
He's the same prick
who put you in that chair.

34:52.758 --> 34:55.670
Adams framed you.

34:55.678 --> 34:57.214
I can't prove it yet,

34:57.221 --> 34:59.963
but I got a friend
at the DA's office.

35:00.391 --> 35:02.222
There's a tollbooth photo
of you

35:02.226 --> 35:03.807
the night Rosie Larsen
was murdered.

35:03.811 --> 35:06.769
Put you right
where they needed you.

35:06.772 --> 35:09.889
It was a fake.

35:09.900 --> 35:12.061
So...

35:12.069 --> 35:14.856
Still want to throw in
the towel?

35:27.876 --> 35:30.583
I'm gonna destroy him.

35:39.722 --> 35:42.429
[ Papers rustle]

35:52.526 --> 35:54.733
[Thud, glass shatters]

36:20.512 --> 36:22.503
[Thud]

36:22.514 --> 36:24.425
Who's there?!

36:27.853 --> 36:29.138
[ Locks turns ]

36:40.282 --> 36:42.147
[Knock on door]

36:44.119 --> 36:45.108
[Knock on door]

36:45.120 --> 36:46.906
Holder: Linden.

36:51.251 --> 36:52.707
[ Lock turns]

36:54.546 --> 36:56.537
Holder, what are you doing?

36:56.548 --> 37:00.086
Got Alexi in the car.
He wants to talk.

37:01.178 --> 37:02.884
Okay.

37:03.138 --> 37:05.424
Drake: The good news is
the teacher's gonna make it.

37:05.432 --> 37:07.548
Attempted murder charge
has been dropped.

37:07.893 --> 37:10.054
Now, you're still looking
at kidnapping

37:10.062 --> 37:12.018
and aggravated assault,
Mr. Larsen.

37:12.022 --> 37:14.684
And, uh, I'm not
gonna be able to plead this.

37:14.692 --> 37:16.057
We're gonna have to go to trial.

37:16.068 --> 37:17.558
I thought you said
there'd be...

37:17.569 --> 37:20.231
Compassion?
I'm sure hoping for it.

37:20.239 --> 37:24.733
Due to your, um...
Your Circumstances.

37:24.743 --> 37:28.076
These charges...
They're serious.

37:28.080 --> 37:30.537
Probably looking at a year
before this thing goes to trial.

37:30.541 --> 37:32.327
[Sighs]

37:32.334 --> 37:34.325
What about my boys?
My business? | just can't...

37:34.336 --> 37:37.169
I figure you're looking
at three to five years.

37:37.172 --> 37:40.710
I'm sorry. I wish I had
better news for you.

37:41.343 --> 37:43.299
[Sighs]

37:44.638 --> 37:46.970
Alexi: I was gonna
kill Stan Larsen.

37:48.142 --> 37:50.508
I followed him everywhere.

37:50.519 --> 37:53.431
Learned his routine,
watched him day and night.

37:54.022 --> 37:55.933
And then you met Rosie?

37:56.483 --> 37:59.520
[Sighs]

37:59.528 --> 38:02.144
Who was she afraid of
at that ferry?

38:04.366 --> 38:07.358
I-I think it was
another car.

38:07.369 --> 38:11.362
Like in the next lane.
Drop-off lane.

38:11.373 --> 38:14.831
Well, what kind of make?
What color?

38:14.835 --> 38:16.450
[Sighs]

38:18.380 --> 38:21.713
It's black. Town car.

38:21.717 --> 38:23.207
I'm not sure
it was a Cadillac...

38:23.218 --> 38:26.210
Some kind of...
some kind of luxury make.

38:26.221 --> 38:28.007
A rich guy.

38:29.641 --> 38:31.802
Who was inside of it?

38:34.062 --> 38:36.394
I couldn't see.
The windows were tinted.

38:36.398 --> 38:38.104
[ Scoffs ]

38:40.569 --> 38:42.150
[ Door opens ]

38:45.032 --> 38:48.115
[ Door Closes]
You did good, Alexi.

38:51.371 --> 38:55.489
[ "You Wish You Were Red" plays]
I wish you were red I

38:55.501 --> 39:00.495
I you don't know
you're falling in love I

39:00.506 --> 39:06.502
I money's divine I

39:06.512 --> 39:09.879
I darling I

39:09.890 --> 39:13.223
I revolution won't stand I

39:14.311 --> 39:18.145
I you're a Judas
that's hiding in red I

39:18.148 --> 39:20.810
[ Door closes]

39:20.818 --> 39:25.687
I money's divine I

39:25.697 --> 39:28.313
I and please don't say I

39:28.325 --> 39:33.695
I those words that,
oh, stop trying I

39:33.705 --> 39:38.620
I but, baby, don't cry I

39:38.627 --> 39:43.212
I oh, my darling I

